Dagannoth Supreme spawns and roams on the western side of the Dagannoth Kings' lair. The lair is accessible via the [[Kings' ladder]] deep within the [[Waterbirth Island Dungeon]]. A separate lair where players that have a Dagannoth [[Slayer task]] can attack the Kings is accessible by using the "Slayer" option on the ladder. The lair can be peeked at to see if other players are inside it via the ladder and a [[Crack (Waterbirth Island Dungeon)|crack]] inside a safe room nearby the ladder.

==Strategy==
{{Main|Dagannoth Kings/Strategies}}
Dagannoth Supreme is most weak to [[melee]] attacks. The best weapons to use primarily are the [[abyssal whip]] or [[abyssal tentacle|tentacle]] due to its high [[Strength#Strength bonus|Strength bonus]] and fast attack rate, the [[Saradomin godsword]] for its [[special attack]], accuracy, and Strength bonus, and [[Guthan's warspear]], which should only be used in conjunction with the full [[Barrows set]] to heal. If a player does not possess a Saradomin godsword or [[Crystal halberd]], a [[Dragon dagger]] is a good alternative [[special attack]] weapon.

The biggest threat when killing Dagannoth Supreme is that [[Dagannoth Prime]] may respawn while killing Supreme. To save yourself from Prime's hard-hitting magical attacks, turn on [[Protect from Magic]]. You can either stick around or leave up the ladder. Another possible threat is that [[Dagannoth Rex]] may respawn instead of Prime. If this happens and you are a [[mage]], distract him again like in first wave. However, the mage should feel no inclination to kill Rex; just lure him away. Another strategy is to make use of [[Entangle]] or [[ice spells]] to deal with Rex.

